# Netcat and Socat

## What is Netcat

Netcat (nc) is a networking utility for reading and writing data across TCP and UDP connections. It is called the "Swiss Army knife" of networking. Security professionals use it for port scanning, transferring files, creating shells, and setting up listeners.

---

## Installation

```bash
# Most Linux distros
sudo apt install netcat-openbsd

# Check version
nc -h
```

---

## Basic Connection

### Connect to a port (like telnet)

```bash
nc 192.168.1.1 80
```

After connecting, type an HTTP request:
GET / HTTP/1.1

Host: 192.168.1.1
(Press Enter twice)

### Listen on a port

```bash
nc -lvnp 4444
```

| Flag | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `-l` | Listen mode |
| `-v` | Verbose |
| `-n` | No DNS resolution |
| `-p` | Port number |

