## Key Terms

| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| Reverse shell | Target connects back to attacker listener |
| Bind shell | Attacker connects to listener on target |
| TTY | Proper interactive terminal |
| Dumb shell | Basic shell with no tab completion or arrow keys |
| Socat | Advanced version of Netcat with more features |
| SSL | Encrypted connection — hides shell traffic |
| Banner grabbing | Connecting to a port to read the service announcement |
